WEBVTT

00:02.873 --> 00:04.310
It is Friday, December 8...

00:04.310 --> 00:06.315
and you're tuned in to WXOP,
Baltimore's news radio...

00:06.315 --> 00:07.919
serving all of Maryland...

00:07.920 --> 00:09.925
and the greater
Chesapeake region, 2 4-7.

00:09.926 --> 00:11.997
We've got your Friday morning
trouble spots:

00:11.997 --> 00:16.030
a two-car pileup with
a fatality, on the 97 at...

00:18.000 --> 00:24.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:33.756 --> 00:37.755
[ Buzzer]

00:38.670 --> 00:42.703
It's time.

00:55.816 --> 00:57.253
John!

00:57.254 --> 00:58.457
Press got word
you're taking him...

00:58.457 --> 00:59.526
out the Groves
Street exit.

00:59.527 --> 01:01.365
It looks like
Woodstock out there.

01:01.365 --> 01:03.403
I suggest you
postpone the transfer.

01:03.403 --> 01:05.308
We can get him out later
once the crowd disperses.

01:05.308 --> 01:06.310
Transfer me where?

01:06.311 --> 01:07.981
No, they'll
camp out for days.

01:07.982 --> 01:09.286
We're going ahead with it.

01:09.286 --> 01:10.489
John.

01:10.489 --> 01:12.461
John,
what is going on?

01:12.462 --> 01:15.235
Mr. Wells! Mr. Wells!

01:15.235 --> 01:16.605
Why did you do it?

01:16.606 --> 01:17.909
All right, back up!

01:17.909 --> 01:18.978
Give him some room.

01:18.979 --> 01:20.048
Come on, clear out.

01:20.049 --> 01:22.354
Back up.

01:22.355 --> 01:25.497
Al.

01:25.497 --> 01:26.833
Down!

01:26.833 --> 01:30.832
Weapon!

01:31.012 --> 01:35.011
[ Yelling ]

01:41.674 --> 01:45.673
[ Voice Echoing ]
Somebody call a medic!

01:46.922 --> 01:50.921
[ Heartbeat ]

01:53.239 --> 01:57.238
[ Heartbeat Slowing ]

02:02.496 --> 02:06.495
[ Heartbeat Stops ]

03:32.641 --> 03:34.947
[ Buzzer]

03:34.948 --> 03:37.086
John...

03:37.086 --> 03:39.426
Do you recognize
this, Mr. Wells?

03:39.427 --> 03:42.568
Have you
seen it before?

03:42.568 --> 03:46.567
Um... yes. Who are you?

03:47.014 --> 03:48.116
Don't even...

03:48.116 --> 03:49.653
- Martin.
-John, what am I doing here?

03:49.654 --> 03:51.692
I'm in this cell,
I don't know where I am...

03:51.693 --> 03:52.863
or how I even got here...

03:52.863 --> 03:54.400
and everyone's acting like...

03:54.400 --> 03:56.740
Swear to God,
on top of everything else,
do not play this with me.

03:56.740 --> 03:58.076
I will not be party...

03:58.076 --> 04:01.218
to some half-assed,
1 1 th-hour insanity defense.

04:01.219 --> 04:02.789
What? John...

04:02.790 --> 04:06.789
It's time to start
telling me the truth!

04:10.143 --> 04:13.852
This key card, Mr. Wells...

04:13.852 --> 04:15.691
You do recognize it.

04:15.692 --> 04:16.962
Is that correct?

04:16.962 --> 04:18.498
Yes, it's the swipe card...

04:18.498 --> 04:20.803
that they use
at the apartment building.

04:20.805 --> 04:22.308
For all I know, it's mine.

04:22.309 --> 04:26.308
It is yours.

04:27.590 --> 04:31.133
It was found in the dumpster
behind the Strand Hotel.

04:31.133 --> 04:33.238
You tossed it there,
didn't you?

04:33.239 --> 04:34.676
You had just enough time...

04:34.676 --> 04:36.648
to drive to Baltimore
and commit the murder.

04:36.649 --> 04:38.352
Wait. Murder? What murder?

04:38.352 --> 04:40.157
Then drive back to D.C.

04:40.158 --> 04:41.294
toss the key card.

04:41.294 --> 04:43.232
That way, you could
claim it was stolen.

04:43.233 --> 04:45.238
Make it look like
you spent your whole night...

04:45.238 --> 04:46.975
watching pay-per-view
in your hotel room.

04:46.976 --> 04:48.847
Right?

04:48.847 --> 04:52.846
Please...

04:53.160 --> 04:57.136
What murder?
What is he talking about?

04:57.137 --> 05:01.136
Well, maybe this will
jog your memory, buddy.

05:02.184 --> 05:06.183
Vickie.

05:09.169 --> 05:11.241
My wife.

05:11.242 --> 05:15.241
This isn't happening.

05:16.122 --> 05:20.121
This is not happening.

05:22.004 --> 05:26.003
Court van is waiting.

06:15.716 --> 06:17.621
All right... dignity.

06:17.622 --> 06:20.029
That is your strong suit.

06:20.029 --> 06:21.465
Play it.

06:21.465 --> 06:23.002
Don't lower your eyes.

06:23.003 --> 06:24.507
It makes you look guilty.

06:24.507 --> 06:26.579
Now, we drew Judge Kinberg.

06:26.580 --> 06:29.186
What's your relationship
with him?

06:29.186 --> 06:30.489
Benjamin?

06:30.490 --> 06:32.495
First-name basis.
Excellent.

06:32.495 --> 06:34.567
[ Bailiff]
All rise.

06:34.568 --> 06:36.707
I would remind the
members of the gallery...

06:36.707 --> 06:39.547
to turn off all cellular phones
and paging devices.

06:39.548 --> 06:40.718
Al?

06:40.718 --> 06:43.157
What?

06:43.157 --> 06:44.728
He shot me.

06:44.729 --> 06:47.235
Who?

06:47.235 --> 06:48.438
Your father-in-law?

06:48.438 --> 06:49.608
What are you
talking about?

06:49.608 --> 06:52.750
Circuit Court, Department 6-B
is now in session...

06:52.751 --> 06:55.224
the Honorable
Benjamin Kinberg presiding.

06:55.224 --> 06:57.195
Thursday,
the seventh day of December.

06:57.195 --> 06:58.499
Thursday?

06:58.500 --> 06:59.770
It's not Thursday.

06:59.770 --> 07:00.772
Shh!

07:00.772 --> 07:02.342
It's Saturday.

07:02.343 --> 07:03.513
Yesterday was Friday and...

07:03.513 --> 07:04.615
Today is Thursday.

07:04.616 --> 07:07.289
There's no court
on Saturday.

07:07.290 --> 07:10.565
You know that.

07:10.565 --> 07:12.804
Martin, do you feel all right?

07:12.805 --> 07:14.576
[Judge Pounds Gavel ]

07:14.576 --> 07:18.575
Case Number 8ABX03:
District v. Martin Wells.

07:20.459 --> 07:23.600
Charge of
first-degree murder.

07:23.601 --> 07:25.606
The defense has requested
a hearing on bail?

07:25.606 --> 07:26.976
Yes, Your Honor, we have.

07:26.976 --> 07:29.483
As I'm sure you'd agree,
Mr. Wells' status...

07:29.484 --> 07:30.954
as a prosecutor
makes him a target.

07:30.954 --> 07:32.491
The court puts
his life in danger...

07:32.492 --> 07:33.661
by keeping him
in custody.

07:33.661 --> 07:34.831
Your Honor,
I have the assurances...

07:34.831 --> 07:36.301
of the Baltimore
Department of Corrections...

07:36.301 --> 07:40.334
that Mr. Wells' safety while
in custody is not a concern.

07:40.412 --> 07:42.819
Furthermore, as Your Honor
will certainly agree...

07:42.819 --> 07:44.089
Mr. Wells is an upstanding...

07:44.090 --> 07:47.699
citizen and a respected member
of the Maryland Bar...

07:47.699 --> 07:50.106
held in high esteem
by all his peers.

07:50.106 --> 07:53.447
Your Honor, with cold
calculation, Martin Wells...

07:53.448 --> 07:56.456
brutally stabbed his wife
in their own home.

07:56.456 --> 07:58.728
He poses a threat to the public
and should be denied bail.

07:58.729 --> 08:01.436
He doesn't pose a threat
to anyone, Your Honor...

08:01.436 --> 08:03.006
and he has two small children...

08:03.007 --> 08:04.511
who need him at home.

08:04.512 --> 08:05.647
Why?

08:05.648 --> 08:07.486
Because their mom's not around.

08:07.486 --> 08:10.761
Ms. Carter.

08:10.761 --> 08:13.168
Martin, I can't tell
you how sorry I am...

08:13.168 --> 08:15.641
to see you on that
side of the aisle.

08:15.642 --> 08:18.850
I hope you'll forgive me
when I do exactly what you...

08:18.850 --> 08:20.520
as a prosecutor, would demand.

08:20.521 --> 08:21.825
Bail is denied.

08:21.825 --> 08:23.796
I will, however...

08:23.797 --> 08:25.936
order Mr. Wells transferred
to a more secure...

08:25.936 --> 08:27.974
facility in the interest
of his safety.

08:27.975 --> 08:29.980
Transferred?

08:29.980 --> 08:31.450
No, Ben.

08:31.451 --> 08:32.855
You can't do that.

08:32.855 --> 08:34.258
I can't be transferred.

08:34.259 --> 08:35.128
He'll kill me.

08:35.128 --> 08:36.899
Tomorrow morning--

08:36.899 --> 08:38.236
if today
is really Thursday--

08:38.236 --> 08:40.642
then tomorrow is Friday...

08:40.643 --> 08:41.947
and that's
when he's going to do it.

08:41.947 --> 08:43.918
He's going to shoot me
as I'm being transferred.

08:43.918 --> 08:45.054
Bailiff.

08:45.055 --> 08:46.692
You don't understand!

08:46.693 --> 08:48.196
It'll happen!

08:48.196 --> 08:50.201
It'll happen!

08:50.202 --> 08:51.639
Judge, listen to me!

08:51.639 --> 08:53.877
Ben, it'll happen!

08:53.878 --> 08:57.877
He's going to kill me! Ben!

09:09.956 --> 09:11.626
Mr. Wells...

09:11.627 --> 09:15.203
we understand that you had
an interesting morning in court.

09:15.203 --> 09:17.710
What is it that you'd like
to speak with us about?

09:17.710 --> 09:19.180
You'reJohn's partner?

09:19.181 --> 09:20.918
For God sakes,
Martin.

09:20.919 --> 09:22.791
Agent Scully. You know that.

09:22.791 --> 09:24.194
You met her yesterday.

09:24.194 --> 09:25.664
Yesterday?

09:25.665 --> 09:27.870
Yeah. Yesterday.

09:27.870 --> 09:29.040
Wednesday.

09:29.040 --> 09:30.310
Wednesday?

09:30.311 --> 09:32.851
Are you saying
that you don't remember?

09:32.851 --> 09:35.691
What is the last thing
that you do remember?

09:35.692 --> 09:37.797
Being shot by my father-in-law.

09:37.797 --> 09:40.270
You're wasting our time.

09:40.271 --> 09:41.541
Listen.

09:41.541 --> 09:45.551
I don't know
what I experienced.

09:45.552 --> 09:49.551
But what if
it was a premonition?

09:51.535 --> 09:55.534
A glimpse of the future.

09:56.516 --> 10:00.526
I mean, you do hear
about these kind of things.

10:00.526 --> 10:04.525
Yes... you do.

10:07.044 --> 10:11.077
Mr. Wells,
this shooting aside...

10:11.289 --> 10:14.162
is there anything else
that you remember before that?

10:14.163 --> 10:18.162
Um... I was in D.C...

10:20.981 --> 10:23.186
uh... for a sentencing hearing.

10:23.187 --> 10:26.697
I was staying at
the Strand Hotel like you said.

10:26.697 --> 10:29.337
That was three days ago,
Mr. Wells.

10:29.338 --> 10:32.178
Are you telling us that...

10:32.179 --> 10:35.587
you don't remember
anything else?

10:35.587 --> 10:39.631
Not the murder of your wife?

10:39.632 --> 10:41.168
No.

10:41.169 --> 10:42.473
Out of the blue.

10:42.473 --> 10:43.743
Charged with murder.

10:43.743 --> 10:45.446
You wake up one morning...

10:45.447 --> 10:48.021
and you can't
remember a damn thing.

10:48.022 --> 10:49.759
Martin, you
haven't offered us...

10:49.760 --> 10:52.600
one scrap of evidence
to support your story.

10:52.601 --> 10:54.673
Now, as your friend,
I'm going to listen...

10:54.673 --> 10:57.647
to anything you have to say,
but I will not be lied to.

10:57.647 --> 10:59.384
I'm not lying to you.

10:59.385 --> 11:02.192
You're talking to me
about key cards.

11:02.193 --> 11:04.332
I'm sitting in a jail cell.

11:04.333 --> 11:06.371
I don't understand any of this.

11:06.371 --> 11:08.609
I don't understand any of this.

11:08.610 --> 11:12.454
But I did not...

11:12.455 --> 11:16.398
kill Vickie.

11:16.398 --> 11:20.375
If you truly don't remember...

11:20.376 --> 11:24.375
then how can you be certain
that you didn't?

12:19.670 --> 12:23.669
Courtney! Haley!

12:26.956 --> 12:28.761
Hey, guys!

12:28.761 --> 12:31.969
Oh!

12:31.970 --> 12:35.613
It's so good to see you.

12:35.613 --> 12:37.986
Wh...?! Come on!
Come on, give Daddy a big hug.

12:37.986 --> 12:41.985
Hug your father, ninas.

12:43.868 --> 12:47.845
Mmm...

12:47.846 --> 12:49.149
How are they holding up?

12:49.149 --> 12:51.589
Good. Good, Mr. Wells.

12:51.589 --> 12:54.496
They want to know
when you're coming home.

12:54.497 --> 12:56.669
Oh. See, um...

12:56.670 --> 12:59.010
Daddy has some things
that he has to do--

12:59.010 --> 13:01.015
very, very
important things.

13:01.016 --> 13:02.987
That's why I have
to be here...

13:02.987 --> 13:05.761
right now, but then,
guess what?

13:05.762 --> 13:06.897
I'll be coming home.

13:06.898 --> 13:10.897
Grandpa says they won't
let you come home.

13:21.070 --> 13:25.069
Oh...

13:33.103 --> 13:36.812
[ Gasps ]

13:36.812 --> 13:39.920
Trina, I need you to get me
something out of the apartment--

13:39.920 --> 13:43.919
something from the girls' room.

13:51.050 --> 13:55.049
Thank you.

14:01.847 --> 14:04.520
Why didn't you mention this
to me before the bail hearing?

14:04.520 --> 14:08.553
I hadn't even met you
before the bail hearing.

14:09.133 --> 14:10.938
Nanny-cam.

14:10.938 --> 14:14.937
Oh, Martin, I wish you'd talked
to me about this before.

14:15.049 --> 14:17.020
I really don't know
if this is a great idea.

14:17.021 --> 14:18.793
This tape may have
the murderer on it.

14:18.793 --> 14:20.263
Whatever happens to be
on that tape...

14:20.263 --> 14:22.235
you know that I
am an officer of the court.

14:22.236 --> 14:24.174
I have to share this
with the prosecution.

14:24.174 --> 14:25.878
You think I'm guilty?

14:25.879 --> 14:29.878
Let's... let's clear
this up right now.

14:31.628 --> 14:35.661
Here.

14:36.540 --> 14:38.379
My apartment.

14:38.379 --> 14:39.916
That... that's the girls' room...

14:39.917 --> 14:41.955
and this must be
the police investigation.

14:41.956 --> 14:44.931
What time did
the murder occur?

14:44.931 --> 14:47.537
The official report
has the police arriving...

14:47.537 --> 14:50.912
at your apartment at
6:20 a.m. Monday morning.

14:50.913 --> 14:53.218
Your key card
was used at 4:1 7.

14:53.219 --> 14:56.661
Which means the killer
is somewhere in-between.

14:56.662 --> 15:00.661
Wait.
There's your wife.

15:07.324 --> 15:11.323
Um... we must
have missed something.

15:14.678 --> 15:16.483
Right there.

15:16.483 --> 15:20.482
Martin, that's you.

16:00.235 --> 16:03.176
[ Door Buzzes ]

16:03.176 --> 16:05.582
I'm not going.

16:05.582 --> 16:06.919
How's that?

16:06.919 --> 16:08.422
I told you. This is the day.

16:08.423 --> 16:09.559
If I go, I'll get shot.

16:09.560 --> 16:10.695
You cannot transfer me.

16:10.696 --> 16:11.698
I don't plan to.

16:11.698 --> 16:15.697
Your lawyers want to see you.

16:17.949 --> 16:20.422
[ Whispers ]

16:20.422 --> 16:22.561
There's my favorite client.

16:22.562 --> 16:23.697
Martin, you holding up
all right?

16:23.698 --> 16:26.839
Brent, uh...
I've been better.

16:26.839 --> 16:30.081
We're going to beat this thing.
Guaranteed.

16:30.082 --> 16:31.552
Martin, I have here
one of the finest...

16:31.552 --> 16:33.490
criminal defense
specialists in the country.

16:33.491 --> 16:34.460
I want you to meet...

16:34.460 --> 16:36.665
We met. I've been thinking
all night about the tape...

16:36.666 --> 16:40.676
and I don't see you having to
turn it over to the prosecution.

16:40.677 --> 16:42.047
I'm sorry?

16:42.047 --> 16:44.454
I obviously showed you that tape
in a good faith effort...

16:44.454 --> 16:46.659
to clear my name,
not as an admission of guilt.

16:46.660 --> 16:48.130
Um...

16:48.131 --> 16:50.504
Mr. Wells,
I'm Janet Wilson.

16:50.504 --> 16:54.503
I don't think we've met.

16:56.387 --> 17:00.386
Martin, what is
all this about a videotape?

17:01.166 --> 17:05.199
The... nanny-cam tape.

17:07.885 --> 17:10.223
That's why you're here, right?

17:10.223 --> 17:12.931
I'm here to introduce you
to your new attorney.

17:12.931 --> 17:15.203
We met yesterday at the bail
hearing. Don't you remember?

17:15.204 --> 17:19.203
Martin, the bail hearing
is set for tomorrow.

17:20.185 --> 17:22.223
[ Martin ]
What day is this?

17:22.223 --> 17:26.222
What... day of the week...
is this?

17:26.836 --> 17:29.007
Wednesday.
Wednesday the sixth.

17:29.008 --> 17:30.813
Yesterday you told me
it was Thursday.

17:30.813 --> 17:34.723
The day before that
it was Friday.

17:34.724 --> 17:38.723
It's backwards.

17:39.002 --> 17:41.776
Everything's going backwards.

17:41.777 --> 17:44.583
Martin, I think we should
have you speak to someone.

17:44.583 --> 17:46.053
You're under a hell
of a lot of stress.

17:46.054 --> 17:48.961
Being locked up in this cesspool
really doesn't help.

17:48.962 --> 17:51.836
We can have you out of here
by tomorrow afternoon.

17:51.837 --> 17:53.842
The prosecution's case
is weak to say the least.

17:53.842 --> 17:56.348
They have no physical evidence
tying you to the crime scene.

17:56.349 --> 17:57.385
Plus, they don't have
the key card...

17:57.385 --> 18:01.161
that was used to access
your apartment building.

18:01.162 --> 18:03.836
[ Exhales Sharply ]

18:03.836 --> 18:05.941
The key card.

18:05.942 --> 18:09.941
Without it,
they've got nothing.

18:39.600 --> 18:40.870
[ Man ] Oh, yeah.

18:40.870 --> 18:42.307
[ Laughs ]

18:42.307 --> 18:44.478
Somebody likes you,
my brother.

18:44.479 --> 18:47.019
[ Chuckles ]

18:47.019 --> 18:48.055
Come on, man.

18:48.056 --> 18:49.392
I'm just messing
with you.

18:49.392 --> 18:52.166
What, you ain't got
no sense of humor, counselor?

18:52.167 --> 18:54.607
Do I know you?

18:54.607 --> 18:57.513
No, you don't know me.

18:57.514 --> 18:59.453
Damn sure put me
in here, though.

18:59.454 --> 19:01.425
Possession with intent.

19:01.425 --> 19:03.297
And concealed weapon.

19:03.297 --> 19:04.533
Mm-hmm.

19:04.533 --> 19:07.040
That concealed weapon
was a pipe wrench.

19:07.041 --> 19:09.046
I was on my way
to my baby's mama's house...

19:09.046 --> 19:11.552
to unstick the Pepsi caps from
out her garbage disposer...

19:11.552 --> 19:13.959
but I told you all that!

19:13.960 --> 19:17.201
''Concealed weapon'' added six
months to my sentence, man.

19:17.201 --> 19:18.303
You remember my name?

19:18.304 --> 19:19.574
No, I don't remember
your name.

19:19.574 --> 19:22.048
All I needed to know about
you was that you broke the law.

19:22.048 --> 19:23.651
I broke the law.

19:23.652 --> 19:27.651
Well, then, I guess that
makes you ''Wife Killer, Esq.''

19:29.201 --> 19:33.234
[ Laughs ]

19:45.177 --> 19:46.848
Yo! Pick 'em up...

19:46.849 --> 19:50.848
you stumbling bitch.

19:53.333 --> 19:57.332
[ Prisoner]
Come on.

20:05.599 --> 20:08.306
[ Screams ]

20:08.307 --> 20:12.306
[ Basketball Bouncing ]

20:12.552 --> 20:16.551
[ Moaning ]

20:17.198 --> 20:19.203
[ Buzzer Sounds ]

20:19.203 --> 20:23.202
[ Door Opens ]

20:25.253 --> 20:26.255
[ Buzzer Sounds ]

20:26.255 --> 20:27.558
[ Door Closes ]

20:27.559 --> 20:28.561
Aw, geez, Martin.

20:28.561 --> 20:29.563
Your face.

20:29.564 --> 20:31.769
It's all right.

20:31.770 --> 20:33.542
Appreciate your coming
to see me.

20:33.542 --> 20:36.382
Agent Scully, I especially
wanted to talk to you.

20:36.383 --> 20:37.485
It's nice to meet you.

20:37.486 --> 20:40.694
I'm sorry it's not under
better circumstances.

20:40.694 --> 20:44.069
This is the day we meet.

20:44.070 --> 20:46.844
Something is happening to me...

20:46.845 --> 20:50.844
something I need to try
to explain to you both.

20:53.596 --> 20:56.704
I'm moving backward in time.

20:56.705 --> 20:59.713
Every morning I wake up,
it's the day before.

20:59.713 --> 21:01.751
For me, yesterday
was Thursday...

21:01.751 --> 21:05.126
the day before that was Friday,
only it's all new to me.

21:05.127 --> 21:08.436
Every single morning I wake up,
I can only remember...

21:08.437 --> 21:10.542
what's happened
the following day.

21:10.542 --> 21:14.151
Agent Scully, would you
mind taking a closer look...

21:14.151 --> 21:17.058
at his injuries,
maybe check his scalp?

21:17.059 --> 21:19.899
I know this all sounds crazy.

21:19.900 --> 21:22.908
But I'm telling you the truth.

21:22.908 --> 21:24.880
This cut, for instance.

21:24.881 --> 21:28.056
It was on my cheek
when I woke up yesterday.

21:28.056 --> 21:30.963
I woke up this morning,
it wasn't there.

21:30.964 --> 21:33.036
But then this afternoon...

21:33.037 --> 21:34.740
I got cut.

21:34.741 --> 21:37.849
I killed a spider
in my cell yesterday.

21:37.849 --> 21:40.189
First thing this morning,
I woke up, it's back again.

21:40.189 --> 21:43.264
Because it happened
the day before.

21:43.264 --> 21:44.934
I haven't actually
killed it yet.

21:44.935 --> 21:46.305
Mr. Wells, are
you saying that...

21:46.306 --> 21:49.080
you don't remember the day that
your wife was murdered?

21:49.080 --> 21:53.079
I'm talking about
two days ago, Monday.

21:53.625 --> 21:57.624
No, I don't... remember it...

21:58.739 --> 22:02.772
because for me,
it hasn't happened yet.

22:05.959 --> 22:09.067
You do realize that, uh...

22:09.068 --> 22:13.067
you're not going to be able
to prove this, right?

22:13.246 --> 22:15.619
I mean, if, uh...

22:15.619 --> 22:19.629
if tomorrow
is really the day before today...

22:19.630 --> 22:23.629
then we won't
have had this conversation.

22:25.812 --> 22:27.349
Oh, for crying out loud.

22:27.350 --> 22:29.656
It means you're going to have
to tell us all over again.

22:29.657 --> 22:31.394
Yeah, well, uh...

22:31.395 --> 22:35.394
make sure I skip
that freaking meeting.

22:43.861 --> 22:47.860
Mr. Wells, let's say
that all this is true.

22:50.346 --> 22:52.986
Why do you think
it's happening?

22:52.987 --> 22:56.328
I don't know.

22:56.329 --> 22:58.568
There has to be a reason.

22:58.568 --> 23:01.408
What reason?

23:01.409 --> 23:05.408
Something...

23:05.553 --> 23:09.552
I'm meant to understand?

23:11.336 --> 23:15.335
Although I don't know
what it could be.

23:16.049 --> 23:20.048
Maybe you already have
the answer within you.

23:30.455 --> 23:32.493
[ Buzzer Sounds ]

23:32.493 --> 23:36.492
[ Door Closes ]

23:47.234 --> 23:49.974
I'd really prefer to stay
while you do this.

23:49.974 --> 23:51.677
Martin.

23:51.678 --> 23:55.221
I can take you through
the chain of evidence.

23:55.221 --> 23:59.220
I think I've done this before,
thank you, Ms. Wilson.

24:08.691 --> 24:12.690
Mmm-hmm, looking for some
loopholes, huh?

24:13.605 --> 24:17.515
Yeah, man, get yourself
out of here.

24:17.516 --> 24:20.624
They just praying that you find
that one little technicality...

24:20.624 --> 24:21.794
so they can let you go.

24:21.794 --> 24:23.531
I'm not looking
for technicalities.

24:23.532 --> 24:25.737
Well, what are
you looking for, brother?

24:25.738 --> 24:26.673
The truth.

24:26.673 --> 24:27.775
The truth?

24:27.776 --> 24:29.615
[ Laughs ]

24:29.615 --> 24:31.887
You better stick
to the technicalities!

24:31.888 --> 24:34.427
The truth is going
to keep you in here...

24:34.428 --> 24:36.333
and make you
somebody's bitch...

24:36.333 --> 24:39.207
that's what the truth's
going to do.

24:39.208 --> 24:41.648
So put on that
engineering hat, CaseyJones...

24:41.648 --> 24:44.321
because you've got a whole lot
of trains to be pulling...

24:44.322 --> 24:45.859
[ Laughs ]

24:45.859 --> 24:47.496
[ Imitates Train Whistle ]

24:47.497 --> 24:51.496
[ Imitates Train Chugging ]

24:53.881 --> 24:57.880
The truth!

25:13.835 --> 25:17.834
[ Sobs ]

25:28.676 --> 25:32.709
[ Cries ]

25:42.479 --> 25:46.478
I know who did it.

26:18.009 --> 26:20.348
[ Reporter] ...claims he arrived home
from a business trip...

26:20.348 --> 26:22.955
to discover the body of his wife
in their living room.

26:22.956 --> 26:24.626
Apparently, Wells
is now in seclusion...

26:24.626 --> 26:25.762
at the home of a friend.

26:25.763 --> 26:27.968
Baltimore Police
are giving no indication...

26:27.969 --> 26:30.007
whether he is a suspect
in the murder...

26:30.008 --> 26:32.782
or if there are indeed
any suspects at this time.

26:32.782 --> 26:35.222
However, Channel 9 News has
learned police are focusing...

26:35.223 --> 26:37.027
their investigation
on the whereabouts...

26:37.027 --> 26:39.132
of an electronic key card,
much like this one.

26:39.132 --> 26:41.438
The card in question
belongs to Martin Wells.

26:41.439 --> 26:44.279
It was used by the killer
to enter the Calvert House...

26:44.280 --> 26:47.421
apartment building
through the garage entrance.

26:47.421 --> 26:50.195
Wells claims no knowledge of the
whereabouts of his key card...

26:50.196 --> 26:51.866
Not something
you want to wake up to.

26:51.867 --> 26:53.972
- ...and suggests
it may have been stolen.
- [ Clicks ]

26:53.973 --> 26:55.845
How you feeling?

26:55.845 --> 26:57.448
Disconnected from reality...

26:57.449 --> 27:01.482
but I guess I'd better
get used to it.

27:02.296 --> 27:05.337
Oh, um... thank you.

27:05.337 --> 27:09.180
I assume you... let me
spend the night here, right?

27:09.181 --> 27:11.186
Thank you.

27:11.186 --> 27:13.926
Like I said, no problem.

27:13.927 --> 27:17.069
So that makes today--
Tuesday...

27:17.069 --> 27:21.068
the day after the murder.

27:21.781 --> 27:25.780
John...

27:25.994 --> 27:30.037
I know who did it now.

27:30.037 --> 27:32.309
You know who killed Vickie?

27:32.310 --> 27:36.320
Mmm. Latino, maybe 40,
five-ten, 1 85 pounds.

27:36.321 --> 27:39.362
He's got a tattoo
of a spiderweb on his left hand.

27:39.362 --> 27:43.205
Martin, last night you told me
you had no idea who did this.

27:43.206 --> 27:46.381
Yeah, now I do.

27:46.381 --> 27:48.553
Well, trust me. I mean,
I-I don't know his name...

27:48.554 --> 27:51.061
but you can find him
in the Baltimore City lockup.

27:51.061 --> 27:55.060
Call them. They can I.D. him
based on what I just told you.

28:03.963 --> 28:05.266
[ Remote Control Clicks ]

28:05.266 --> 28:06.636
[ Al ]
I just want to say...

28:06.636 --> 28:10.213
my daughter was
an exceptional person...

28:10.213 --> 28:11.516
[ Sighs ]

28:11.517 --> 28:14.658
...one who was loved
by everyone who knew her.

28:14.658 --> 28:17.700
[ Reporter] Sir, have the police
identified any suspects...

28:17.700 --> 28:19.237
in your daughter's death?

28:19.238 --> 28:21.744
They're not telling us much.

28:21.744 --> 28:25.119
What about rumors that your
son-in-law is the prime suspect?

28:25.120 --> 28:29.153
What are your thoughts on that?

28:29.833 --> 28:33.409
Reporting from
the Calvert House Apartments...

28:33.409 --> 28:34.511
this is Brian Blakley.

28:34.512 --> 28:35.749
Back to you in the studio.

28:35.749 --> 28:37.520
No prisoner fitting
that description...

28:37.520 --> 28:39.492
has been processed
in the past 36 hours.

28:39.492 --> 28:40.494
He's in there.

28:40.495 --> 28:41.765
He's got to be there.

28:41.765 --> 28:45.764
Sorry, Martin, he's not.

28:49.219 --> 28:50.522
It must be too soon.

28:50.522 --> 28:53.597
He must not get arrested
until later today-- Tuesday.

28:53.598 --> 28:57.374
That's how he could have been
with me in lockup on Wednesday.

28:57.374 --> 28:59.747
Martin, you have
seriously lost me.

28:59.747 --> 29:02.722
If you're trying to admit
something to me or to yourself...

29:02.722 --> 29:04.660
I want you to just
come out with it.

29:04.661 --> 29:08.660
There's a reason all this
is happening.

29:09.307 --> 29:12.816
Maybe I already have the answer.

29:12.816 --> 29:14.655
Well, how's that?

29:14.655 --> 29:18.654
There's something
in my apartment that
you need to see,John.

29:26.854 --> 29:28.458
Where is it?

29:28.458 --> 29:32.457
Uh, the girls'
bedroom, right there.

29:53.092 --> 29:55.164
[ Glass Shattering ]

29:55.164 --> 29:55.999
[ Screams ]

29:56.000 --> 30:00.033
Martin?
Is this it?

30:12.611 --> 30:16.621
My daughters were at their
grandparents'... thank God.

30:16.622 --> 30:18.828
Their bedroom door was open...

30:18.829 --> 30:22.103
with a clear view
of the front hallway.

30:22.103 --> 30:24.075
The nanny-cam is
motion-activated...

30:24.076 --> 30:27.919
so it should have caught anyone
coming in or out of the house.

30:27.919 --> 30:29.055
[ Tape Rewinds ]

30:29.056 --> 30:30.593
There I am.

30:30.594 --> 30:34.337
Nobody else on the tape
between my wife and the police.

30:34.337 --> 30:38.336
I don't understand it.

30:38.916 --> 30:42.915
I'd say this makes you look
more innocent than guilty.

30:43.863 --> 30:47.105
Look, there-- in the mirror...

30:47.105 --> 30:48.842
...the sun.

30:48.843 --> 30:50.948
Your wife comes home...

30:50.949 --> 30:54.859
before the murderer enters
the building at 4:1 7 a.m.

30:54.859 --> 30:58.702
Her time of death is
fixed shortly after that
well before sunrise.

30:58.703 --> 31:02.702
You came home later,
when the sun was already up.

31:05.287 --> 31:07.727
The killer turned off the tape.

31:07.727 --> 31:10.668
The only question is how?

31:10.668 --> 31:12.873
There's a remote control
for the nanny-cam.

31:12.874 --> 31:15.080
It's in a drawer
by the front door...

31:15.081 --> 31:18.422
but nobody else knew
about it except for...

31:18.423 --> 31:20.160
Vickie...

31:20.161 --> 31:21.398
and me.

31:21.398 --> 31:25.397
Are you sure about that?

31:27.347 --> 31:31.257
[ Knocks On Door]

31:31.258 --> 31:32.862
FBI!

31:32.862 --> 31:34.198
I saw your curtains move.

31:34.199 --> 31:35.436
I know you're in there.

31:35.436 --> 31:37.876
[ Door Unlatches ]

31:37.876 --> 31:39.179
M-Mr. Wells, I...

31:39.179 --> 31:42.154
Trina, you knew about
the nanny-cam, didn't you?

31:42.154 --> 31:44.059
You told the
killer about it.

31:44.060 --> 31:47.101
You must have given
him my key card, too.

31:47.101 --> 31:50.076
Mr. Wells, I-I-I wasn't
even there that night.

31:50.076 --> 31:54.075
First thing you're supposed
to say is: ''What nanny-cam?''

32:01.172 --> 32:02.442
Is this your guy?

32:02.442 --> 32:03.444
[ Trina Crying ]

32:03.445 --> 32:05.217
I'm so sorry, Mr. Wells.

32:05.217 --> 32:08.525
He said
he'd hurt my family.

32:08.526 --> 32:12.536
He made me give him
your key card.

32:12.536 --> 32:16.535
[ Trina Sobbing ]

32:19.054 --> 32:23.053
[ Door Closes ]

32:23.199 --> 32:25.004
His name is Caesar Okompo.

32:25.004 --> 32:28.045
He's got a full sheet--
assault and narcotics.

32:28.045 --> 32:30.618
He knows the drill.
He's a clam.

32:30.618 --> 32:32.623
We'll have Trina's
testimony against him.

32:32.624 --> 32:33.794
Or maybe we won't.

32:33.794 --> 32:37.203
He's got her so scared
we can't count on her.

32:37.204 --> 32:39.108
[ Phone Rings In Distance ]

32:39.108 --> 32:42.015
John, let me go in
and talk to him.

32:42.016 --> 32:46.015
Please.

32:46.161 --> 32:50.160
He says he only wants
to talk to you.

32:51.743 --> 32:55.776
[ Door Opens ]

33:10.394 --> 33:11.664
Why?

33:11.664 --> 33:13.200
You don't know?

33:13.200 --> 33:15.540
You got my name, my record,
and you can't figure it out?

33:15.540 --> 33:17.745
Caesar Okompo--
I don't know you.

33:17.746 --> 33:19.518
I never prosecuted you.

33:19.518 --> 33:23.328
Hector Okompo, my brother.

33:23.329 --> 33:25.267
What was the charge?

33:25.267 --> 33:26.804
Possession with intent.

33:26.805 --> 33:28.810
$50 worth of rock.

33:28.810 --> 33:30.982
It was his third strike,
remember?

33:30.983 --> 33:32.586
Yeah, I remember.

33:32.587 --> 33:33.456
I did my job.

33:33.456 --> 33:34.491
You sent him up for life!

33:34.492 --> 33:38.235
I did my job!

33:38.235 --> 33:42.234
I do it ten times a week
every week of the year...

33:42.413 --> 33:45.956
and for this,
my wife was murdered?

33:45.956 --> 33:48.662
You take away my dignity,
my reputation, my life...

33:48.663 --> 33:51.470
because your dirtbag brother
is where he belongs?!

33:51.471 --> 33:55.504
Brady v. Maryland.

33:56.418 --> 33:58.322
Hey, you know
what I'm talking about.

33:58.323 --> 33:59.927
Brady v. the State of Maryland.

33:59.927 --> 34:02.667
Prosecution's got to turn over
exonerating evidence.

34:02.668 --> 34:06.667
You had the word of three people
that wasn't Hector's rock.

34:06.846 --> 34:09.453
It was in a jacket
that wasn't even his...

34:09.454 --> 34:11.024
left beside him in the club.

34:11.024 --> 34:12.393
You knew that.

34:12.395 --> 34:14.900
You knew that and you
suppressed the evidence.

34:14.900 --> 34:18.811
Are you trying to tell me
that your brother
is not a drug dealer?

34:18.812 --> 34:21.152
My brother was a busboy
when you sent him up.

34:21.152 --> 34:25.185
He had two strikes on him.
He wasn't dealing no more.

34:26.433 --> 34:30.431
You sent him up
for who he used to be...

34:30.710 --> 34:32.815
and 'cause it was easy.

34:32.817 --> 34:36.815
You broke the law.

34:43.011 --> 34:45.149
I tell you what we'll do.

34:45.150 --> 34:49.149
You're going to be
convicted of my wife's murder
one way or another.

34:49.261 --> 34:52.670
Plead out now and I'll look
into your brother's case.

34:52.670 --> 34:55.712
Maybe I'll find a way to
recommend a reduced sentence.

34:55.712 --> 34:58.052
Time served.

34:58.052 --> 35:02.051
You want justice?
So do I.

35:04.269 --> 35:08.179
My brother is dead.

35:08.179 --> 35:12.178
Hung himself in a jail cell
a couple weeks ago.

35:14.162 --> 35:18.161
Martin... a word.

35:23.921 --> 35:25.693
I'm sorry, Martin.

35:25.693 --> 35:29.369
I tried to talk them out of it,
but they think they have a case.

35:29.370 --> 35:31.208
Sir, turn around, please.

35:31.208 --> 35:33.247
Martin Wells,
you are under arrest...

35:33.247 --> 35:35.118
for the murder of Vickie Wells.

35:35.118 --> 35:37.324
You have the right
to remain silent.

35:37.325 --> 35:39.731
Anything you say can
and will be used...

35:39.731 --> 35:41.335
against you in
a court of law.

35:41.336 --> 35:45.335
You have the right
to an attorney.

36:00.454 --> 36:04.453
[ Mumbling ]

36:17.968 --> 36:19.505
Come on, honey, pick up.

36:19.506 --> 36:21.110
[ Ringing ]

36:21.110 --> 36:22.380
Pick up!

36:22.380 --> 36:23.415
[ Vickie ]
Hey, there.

36:23.416 --> 36:24.418
Vickie...

36:24.419 --> 36:25.689
This is the Wells' residence...

36:25.689 --> 36:27.527
home of Martin, Vickie,
Courtney and Haley.

36:27.527 --> 36:29.198
We can't come to the phone
right now.

36:29.199 --> 36:30.368
So, please leave a message.

36:30.368 --> 36:31.538
[ Beeps ]

36:31.538 --> 36:33.978
Honey, this is Martin.
Pick up the phone.

36:33.978 --> 36:35.983
Vickie, pick up the phone.

36:35.984 --> 36:39.983
Pick up the phone!

36:40.563 --> 36:42.133
It's not 4:00 yet.

36:42.133 --> 36:43.604
Vickie, please,
when you get this...

36:43.605 --> 36:46.178
get out of the apartment,
go to your parents' house...

36:46.178 --> 36:47.247
and wait for me to call.

36:47.248 --> 36:51.247
I'm on my way back to the city.

36:51.492 --> 36:55.525
[ Dog Barking Nearby ]

36:58.646 --> 37:01.219
John, I need your help.

37:01.219 --> 37:05.218
Martin?

37:05.397 --> 37:08.270
Vickie's going to be murdered
inside of two hours.

37:08.271 --> 37:09.741
Vickie? You
mean your wife?

37:09.742 --> 37:11.714
I called the Baltimore Police
but I can't tell...

37:11.714 --> 37:13.084
if they thought
I was a crank.

37:13.084 --> 37:14.421
I need you to call them.

37:14.422 --> 37:16.594
Now, I can describe the suspect,
his name... everything.

37:16.594 --> 37:18.097
Well, how do you
know all this?

37:18.098 --> 37:20.070
No time to explain.
You wouldn't believe it anyway.

37:20.070 --> 37:21.874
Now, Martin, you see,
now, that's a bad sign...

37:21.874 --> 37:23.846
because it's two-
something in the morning.

37:23.847 --> 37:25.484
I haven't seen you
in three years.

37:25.485 --> 37:27.457
You got to give me
something more to go on.

37:27.457 --> 37:30.665
This is all happening
for a reason.

37:30.665 --> 37:34.174
I... I'm being given
a second chance.

37:34.174 --> 37:38.173
A second chance
to do what?

37:38.955 --> 37:41.461
I prosecuted a man
named Hector Okompo.

37:41.461 --> 37:43.233
I suppressed evidence.

37:43.233 --> 37:46.241
See, he was innocent of
the crime he was charged with.

37:46.241 --> 37:47.844
Martin, anything
you say to me...

37:47.845 --> 37:48.914
You have to report.

37:48.915 --> 37:50.385
I put him away,
he died in prison...

37:50.385 --> 37:52.390
his brother wants revenge,
and it is as simple as that.

37:52.391 --> 37:55.231
You could be disbarred for
what you're telling me.

37:55.232 --> 37:57.939
You could go to prison,
lose everything;
do you understand?

37:57.939 --> 38:01.938
I understand
that I can save Vickie.

38:04.290 --> 38:08.289
Hold on a minute.

38:08.568 --> 38:09.871
[ Dial Tone Buzzing ]

38:09.872 --> 38:13.871
[ Phone Tones Beeping ]

38:21.837 --> 38:25.870
[ Indistinct Radio Chatter]

38:33.837 --> 38:37.513
[ Panting ]

38:37.513 --> 38:40.488
[ Relieved Sighing ]

38:40.488 --> 38:43.195
You got here in time.

38:43.196 --> 38:44.532
Are you Martin Wells?

38:44.532 --> 38:45.702
Yeah. Vickie?

38:45.702 --> 38:46.704
Vickie?

38:46.705 --> 38:49.111
There's nobody here.
We checked.

38:49.111 --> 38:51.083
What exactly are
we looking for?

38:51.083 --> 38:53.590
My wife's going
to be attacked here tonight.

38:53.591 --> 38:54.726
It happens...

38:54.726 --> 38:57.667
The killer's going
to use my key card
to enter at 4:1 7.

38:57.668 --> 39:01.667
It's 4:20 now.

39:02.520 --> 39:04.555
I don't understand.

39:04.555 --> 39:06.557
Where is she?

39:06.557 --> 39:08.259
Tell you what.

39:08.259 --> 39:12.252
We'll take a few sweeps
through the neighborhood,
keep our eyes peeled.

39:12.330 --> 39:16.323
We're a phone call away
if you need us.

39:27.712 --> 39:28.713
[ Phone Beeps ]

39:28.713 --> 39:30.014
[ Speed-dialing ]

39:30.014 --> 39:31.315
[ Ringing ]

39:31.315 --> 39:34.585
Come on.
Come on!

39:34.585 --> 39:35.586
[ Al ]
Hello?

39:35.586 --> 39:36.587
Al, it's Martin.

39:36.587 --> 39:37.588
Martin?

39:37.588 --> 39:38.589
What time is it?

39:38.589 --> 39:39.590
Al...

39:39.590 --> 39:40.591
[ Clears Throat ]

39:40.591 --> 39:41.726
is-is Vickie there?

39:41.726 --> 39:43.061
No. The kids are here.

39:43.061 --> 39:44.529
Vickie left hours ago.

39:44.529 --> 39:46.531
- [ Bumping ]
- Isn't she home yet?

39:46.531 --> 39:48.332
[ DoorknobJiggles ]

39:48.332 --> 39:49.467
Martin?

39:49.467 --> 39:53.494
[ Phone Drops In Cradle ]

40:07.652 --> 40:09.387
[ DoorknobJiggling ]

40:09.387 --> 40:13.380
[ Panting ]

40:17.462 --> 40:18.463
[ Screams ]

40:18.463 --> 40:19.664
[ Panting ]

40:19.664 --> 40:21.799
Martin, you scared
the hell out of me!!

40:21.799 --> 40:24.202
Honey, why aren't you
in D.C.?

40:24.202 --> 40:25.436
